{
  "text": "GSH is the most abundant, soluble non-enzymatic antioxidant. It has multifunctional roles as a substrate for glutathione S-transferases (GSTs) and glutathione perox- [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The present study was specifically meant to evaluate salivary and serum MDA and GSH levels in controls, and in oral leukoplakia and OSCC patients.",
  "correct_citation": {
